# Controls what `gcloud builds submit` uploads as the build context.
#
# Without this file, gcloud auto-generates one FROM .gitignore -- and
# .gitignore excludes *.db (to stop local SQLite test files from being
# committed). That silently excluded the pre-built msme_fhc.db from the
# Cloud Build upload too, so the deployed image got an empty auto-created
# SQLite file instead of the real one: "no such table: customers" at
# runtime, not a missing-file error, since sqlite3 happily creates an empty
# db on first connection. This file deliberately does NOT exclude *.db.

.venv
.git
__pycache__
*.pyc
.env
.env.example
demo-deployment.env
tests
.claude
context
cloud-run-url.txt
